  "name": "TelePost Bot",
  "description": "TelePost Bot\nAutomated weekly Telegram channel poster with scheduled publishing, retry logic, and optional inline buttons.\n\nHow it works\nSchedule: Mon–Wed, every 15 minutes between 19:00–21:45 (Europe/Moscow)\n\nFlow:\n\nReads all pending posts from the built-in n8n Data Table\nFilters by current day of week and time (±15 min window)\nApplies 6-day cooldown — a post won't be re-sent within 6 days after publishing\nOptionally attaches an inline URL button if button_text and button_url are provided\nSends the post to a Telegram channel via Bot API\nOn success — records sent_at timestamp in the Data Table\nOn failure — increments retry_count; after 3 failed attempts marks the post as error\n\nData Table: telegram_posts\n\nColumn\tType\tDescription\nchannel_id\tString\tTelegram channel ID or @username\npost_id\tNumber\tUnique post identifier\nday_of_week\tNumber\t0=Sun, 1=Mon, … 6=Sat\ntime\tString\tTarget time, e.g. \"20:45\"\npost_text\tString\tMessage text (HTML supported)\nstatus\tString\tpending or error\nsent_at\tString\tISO timestamp of last send\nretry_count\tNumber\tFailed attempt counter\nbutton_text\tString\tInline button label (optional)\nbutton_url\tString\tInline button URL (optional)\n\nKey behaviors\n\nWeekly recurrence: after sending, sent_at is set and the 6-day cooldown prevents re-sending until the next week\nRetry: up to 3 attempts per post; after 3 failures status changes to error\nTimezone-aware: all time comparisons use Europe/Moscow timezone (server runs in UTC)\nOptional buttons: if both button_text and button_url are filled, an inline URL button is attached to the message.",
  "active": false,
  "isArchived": false,
  "nodes": [
    {
      "parameters": {
        "rule": {
          "interval": [
            {
              "field": "cronExpression",
              "expression": "*/15 19-21 * * 1-3"
            }
          ]
        }
      },
